      "content": "i get the environment thing, but even if it's not biological, it feels like when people talk about \"advancement,\" they are almost always talking about Western Europe or North America. like, the standard for \"modern\" seems to be based on how they built things. doesn't that make the whole concept of a \"primitive\" society kind of a biased way to describe non-Western cultures? it feels like it's just setting them up as \"less than\" because they didn't follow the same path.",
